node.text:
A closer look (see our previous post!) at the print on the back of our Hokusai x Tsuki White T-Shirt..

Katsushika Hokusai (1760 – 1849), was an eccentric Japanese artist, ukiyo-e painter, and printmaker of the Edo period. The Great Wave off Kanagawa is Hokusai’s most famous work. Made originally as a woodblock print for the series Thirty-six views of Mount Fuji, and modernized for Tsuki, it features both the threatening, energetic wave, and the serene, solid Mount Fuji in the distance. 

Shop our entire Hokusai collection, available in a wide size range & shipping mid August, via the link in our bio! #tsukimarket

node.text:
Introducing our new collection: Hokusai x Tsuki

Katsushika Hokusai (1760 – 1849), was an eccentric Japanese artist, ukiyo-e painter, and printmaker of the Edo period. Hokusai is best known for the woodblock print series Thirty-Six Views of Mount Fuji which includes the internationally iconic print The Great Wave off Kanagawa.

Tsuki has reimagined some of Hokusai’s most recognizable pieces, available now, as a very limited production run.

Pieces ship from the UK starting in early August.

Link in bio to shop!
